-- India’s NTPC Seeks 7 Million Tons Imported Coal for Power Plants
-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 2012-10-10T09:54:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-10/india-s-ntpc-seeks-7-million-tons-imported-coal-for-power-plants.html
NTPC Ltd. (NTPC) ,  India ’s largest
electricity generator, is seeking 7 million metric tons of
imported steam coal for 16 plants across the country for
delivery over four months, according to tender  documents  posted
on the utility’s website.  The state-owned company plans to import 16 million tons of
coal in the financial year ending March 2013, Chairman Arup Roy Choudhury said on Sept. 13.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Archana Chaudhary in New Delhi at 
